  "description": [
    "vs alk sii Jlswif OLDEST NEWSPAPER IN ALASKAMEMBER ASSOCIATED PRESS NOMALASKA MONDAY OCTOBER 22 1962 Kennedy Proclaims US Naval Blockade Against Cuba WASHINGTON UP President Kennedy proclaimed a US naval blockade against Cuba tonight saying the Soviets have started to turn Cuba into an offensive mili tary base capable of raining nuc lear destruction on all the Americas In an address prepared for nationwide television and radio delivery Kennedy said the United States would regard any missile launched from Cuba against any nation in the West ern Hemisphere as an attack by the Soviet Union on the United Stales requiring a full retalia tory response upon the Soviet Union But Kennedy in his dramatic report on the intensified buildup in Cuba did not order any direct military action at this time He called upon Soviet Premier Khrushchev to halt this clan estine reckless and provocative threat to world peace and to stable relations between our two nations Kennedy challenged Khrush chev to join in an historic effort to end the arms race The President announced that he has ordered reinforcements to the U S naval base at Guan tanamo Cuba has evacuated de pendents of military personnel from the base"
